Computer Science.description: Computer Science is the foundational study of computation, algorithms, and information systems. Students explore core topics including programming languages, data structures, artificial intelligence, and computer architecture. Graduates are prepared for a wide range of technical careers, such as software engineer, systems analyst, cybersecurity specialist, and data scientist. This major provides a deep theoretical understanding of how computers work, enabling innovation across various industries.

Computer Engineering.description: Software Engineering focuses on the systematic design, development, testing, and maintenance of software systems. It applies engineering principles to the software creation process, covering topics like software development lifecycles, project management, quality assurance, and system architecture. Graduates typically pursue careers as software developers, quality assurance engineers, DevOps specialists, or technical project managers, building scalable and reliable applications.
